🔷 Explanation of Architecture
🔹 1. Region A (Primary Region – Mumbai)
Main application runs here
EC2 instance hosts the web server (Apache)
Root EBS volume stores OS + application
🔹 2. EBS Volume
Attached storage for EC2
Contains application files and configurations
🔹 3. EBS Snapshot
Backup of the EBS volume
Captures complete data state
🔹 4. Cross-Region Copy
Snapshot is copied from:
Region A → Region B
Ensures disaster recovery capability
🔹 5. Region B (Backup Region – Ohio)
Used for recovery during failure
Stores copied snapshot
🔹 6. Restore Process
Create new EBS volume from snapshot
Attach volume to new EC2 instance
🔹 7. EC2 in Region B
New instance created
Restored volume attached
Apache server started
🔹 8. Application Recovery
Application becomes live again
Ensures business continuity
🔥 Key Features of This Architecture

✅ Cross-region disaster recovery
✅ Data backup and restore
✅ High reliability
✅ Minimal downtime
✅ Secure data replication
